Note: An ArrayList usually uses an internal array.
      If that internal array becomes full
      it creates a larger array
      copies the old elements into the new array
      then continues using the new one
      So the dynamic resizing is not free.
      In Java an array can store primitive types directly
      but ArrayList just stores objs!

